<DocsPageTitle>
    Field component
</DocsPageTitle>

<DocsPageParagraph>
    The <Code Tag>Field</Code> is a container for <Code>TextEdit</Code>, <Code>Select</Code>, <Code>DateEdit</Code>,
    <Code>Check</Code>, <Code>MemoEdit</Code>, and optionally for <Code>Button</Code>. Structure is very simple:
</DocsPageParagraph>

<UnorderedList>
    <UnorderedListItem>
        <Code>Field</Code> the main container
        <UnorderedList>
            <UnorderedListItem><Code>FieldLabel</Code> a field label</UnorderedListItem>
            <UnorderedListItem><Code>FieldBody</Code> used only for horizontal fields</UnorderedListItem>
            <UnorderedListItem><Code>FieldHelp</Code> small text bellow the field</UnorderedListItem>
        </UnorderedList>
    </UnorderedListItem>
    <UnorderedListItem>
        <Code>Fields</Code> container used to group several <Code>Field</Code> components
    </UnorderedListItem>
</UnorderedList>

<DocsPageParagraph>
    It is recommended to always place input components inside of a field. That way you will keep the right spacing
    and arrangement between input controls.
</DocsPageParagraph>

